text: Visited twice in this location, there was a line both times but the wait wasn’t bad at all. Moves fast. I got the cheese pizza, I guess it’s the classic must try, that was good. I came back for the got their version of supreme pizza with all the meats & onion, that was really good. Whenever you’re in NYC, Joe’s Pizza is a must have stop.

Joe's Pizza is absolutely delicious—easily the best pizza I’ve ever had! Now I completely understand what all the NYC pizza hype is about. The crust is perfectly crispy, the sauce is rich and flavorful, and the cheese is just the right amount of gooey goodness.
I will make it a point to stop here every time I’m in the area. If you’re in NYC and looking for authentic, mouthwatering pizza, Joe’s is the place to go!

You can tell everything you need to know by the simple and classic cheese pizza, which is what we opted for...Very delicious!

We were in line shortly after opening so it was considered fairly short since it usually is wrapping around the corner. The line goes very quickly either way. A must try when in NYC.

It's a legendary pizza spot. You've heard about this place in movies, TV shows and many celebrities have talked about it. This place is about 50 years old. The lines is huge when you get there, but they move pretty fast. You won't have to wait long for your pizza, and it's definitely worth it. I've tried cheese pizza, and the second one is called Margarita, I believe and erd one was supreme. Supreme, in my opinion, was the best for sure, and I highly recommend trying that. Next time I come to New York, I'm visiting this spot for sure!

I recently visited Joe's Pizza on Broadway in New York, and I have to say, I was blown away! The pizza was absolutely delicious - the crust was perfectly thin and crispy, the sauce was flavorful, and the cheese was gooey and delicious. I opted for a classic pepperoni slice, and it was cooked to perfection.

Honestly, given the prime location right on Broadway, I was expecting the price to be a bit higher. But I was pleasantly surprised at how reasonable it was for such a high-quality slice. It's definitely a great value for your money, especially considering the huge portion sizes.
Joe's Pizza is a must-try for anyone looking for a quick, delicious, and affordable bite in the heart of New York City.

Went for lunch on a Tuesday at around 12:45pm. As usual, there was a line, but it moved really quickly and I was able to get my pizza 10 minutes later. Don’t let the line deter you from trying Joe’s! The pizza is great as always and the staff are nice. Never disappointed. I tried the caprese pizza and it was great!

There are a lot of people inside and outside so it can get hectic, but turnover for seats is quite quick and I got a seat on the bench outside almost right away.

Prepare for long lines during weekend (especially December month). But we took this as a confirmation to wait because long lines are usually a sign of a good place. Pizza was good and we were able to get a standing spot inside to eat.
Would recommend it since it is a known pizza place.

Their pizza made my birthday, and my four year wish to try this place fulfilled. My friends and I shared a pie to get that traditional New York slice. It came out very fast and was tasted excellent. It's an amazing atmosphere in the store and so cool to see so many celebrities on the wall. I can't wait to come back!
My best experience on my trip to San Francisco. Everything was clean and beautiful.

Google is the best. Plain and Simple, I need to work on my resume to work here someday!

Google Inc, if you see this, let me be an ambassador for you 😂😂

Currently a Level 5 Local Guide, so working on becoming the best.

It’s a beautiful campus though!

The 1 thing I need added here though is a Gift Shop… I’d buy so much Google Apparel, would be super cool!

So disapointed! Everywhere in the internet is marked that there is a Google Store (similar to Apple) but no, here is absolutely nothing for public - even the water in the public toilet did not work. My family just told me to sell my android phone ... sad all the way from Switzerland, just to see the (pretty nice) Googleplex from the outside

Horrible treatment. Person at googleplex out of the blue told me: HEY MA’AM - YOU CANNOT GO INTO ANY BUILDING.
Then I asked, can I use the bikes to explore around?
He said, NO!
So I asked, so just walk?
He said, NO! JUST WALK OUTSIDE. HAVE A NICE DAY.
Umm what?.. I felt attacked. He was so rude. No idea why.
There was a shop but security told me that it was not open to the public.
Waste of time. Not much to see. Just a couple of statues and some geese eating grass.

Love this company! Even though visitors cannot enter their office, but you can enjoy the awesome and beautiful outdoor area. It's pretty cool that sometimes you also can see some employees do exercise in the area.

It's a beautiful place but you can't go in anywhere! I would have loved to grab some food, buy some merchandise, or whatever, but everything was closed to the public.

Still, we enjoyed walking around the huge, bustling campus and riding the bikes. The dino was cute too!

A different world, completely unique experience, place where someone doesn't like to come out after entering into the campus.
Good Headquarters, Mountain View (Silicon Valley), California, United States of America

Fun corporate HQ to visit.

Set across lots of buildings and well prepared for tourists.

Would be nice to have a shop open all week. A 'visitor' shop had loads of signs making it clear a member of staff was required to enter.

The Android sculpture garden is pointless so don't bother.

If you're prepared to bend the rules they're unlocked bikes to ride around.

Visiting the Apple Park Visitor Center is an incredible experience for any Apple enthusiast or design lover! From the moment you arrive, you can sense the attention to detail that Apple is famous for. The architecture of the building is sleek, modern, and beautifully integrated into the surrounding landscape, reflecting the innovative spirit of the company.

The open-air terrace offers stunning views of the iconic Apple Park campus, and the augmented reality experience allows you to explore the building in a unique, interactive way. The staff is friendly and knowledgeable, always ready to share interesting facts about the campus and the history of Apple.

The store inside offers exclusive Apple merchandise you won’t find anywhere else, making it a perfect place to pick up a souvenir. The on-site café serves delicious, freshly brewed coffee and a selection of treats, all while you relax in the peaceful atmosphere.

Overall, the Apple Park Visitor Center is a must-visit, whether you’re a tech fan or just appreciate thoughtful design. It’s more than just a visitor center — it’s a reflection of Apple’s vision and commitment to creating beautiful, functional spaces. Highly recommended!

Visit to this center is a memorable experience.Apple Park is 160+ acre headquarters of Apple. A store and cafeteria for public. Most of the space is off limits to the public but you can see an augmented reality layout in the same building as the Apple Store

We ran out of things to do on our last day of our San Francisco trip and we ended going here and loved the experience and a good outing for a couple of hours.

On the ground floor you will find a mind blowing miniature architecture of the Apple space ship/park that can we viewed in a super realistic way using an iPad that will provided for free at the visitor center.

Additionally there is the regular Apple Store in the center of the floor and and the end of the floor is a nice cafe serving delicious beverages with cute Apple logos as your foam design on your coffee.

On the top floor they have a beautiful seating area to take pictures for your gram.

Parking is available for free outside the center but limited.
The visitor park and store is located opposite the Apple Campus with ample parking and a Cafe and a seating area at the top. Good place to hang out and check out the Apple products.
I’m impressed by this place. Minimalism, sustained style, excellent views and nature did not leave me without emotions. I like this place and I definitely want to go back there again.

Slightly underwhelming. If you’re expecting to get a clean look at Apple Park, beware: this is nothing more than a jumbo version of the Apple Store across the street from the campus.

There’s a cool AR feature that lets you do a virtual tour of the campus and a cafe. The bathrooms are clean. There’s a rooftop where you can see some of the campus though.

Here’s a review for Apple Park:

A Stunning Blend of Innovation and Nature

Visiting Apple Park was an incredible experience! The architecture is absolutely breathtaking—the circular “spaceship” design is futuristic and perfectly complements the lush greenery surrounding it. The campus is a seamless blend of cutting-edge technology and sustainable design.

The Apple Park Visitor Center is a must-visit, with its sleek layout, interactive exhibits, and rooftop terrace offering a beautiful view of the campus. An exclusive Apple merchandise add to the charm but too expensive.

This place truly reflects Apple’s commitment to innovation and excellence. If you’re a fan of architecture, technology, or sustainability, Apple Park is worth a visit!

The staff is awesome—knowledgeable and very helpful. Apple is great, as always. However, it would be nice to see more unique items, like they used to offer. (Maybe I would have bought a new Mac or something, but I already have pretty much everything—lol.) It’s a beautiful campus. That’s Apple for you.
